...the fucking thing is sentient.<br><br>
We tried to destroy this level — every method had proven almost inconclusive, but we surely were showing progress. We could not burn the level, we could not destabilize it; hell, we even tried blowing the damn place up. We had even tried harnessing the energy of the ████████████████, and our barbaric efforts to just... 'erase' a level were completely infeasible.<br>We needed to destroy this level. This whole thing is a shitshow of epic proportions.<br><br>
What happened to the Zeta Contingent truly was tragic. Every member, except for me, killed in horrific ways, ways only possible by mere inconvenience. It's like the Backrooms merely killed them for the sake of killing them, as a result of incredible coincidence.<br><br>
I know what it is. The damn thing is sentient. It can feel — it can hear — it knows. It knew of our attempts to combat it, and it gave all of us hell for it.<br><br>
I had found myself back at New London- well, what was left of it — as that whole '[[Phenomenon 12|lights going out]]' bullshit really fucked up everything and stuff. 
And then it sent some insane guy after me. He started hacking his way through everything; despite [[M.E.G|our]] attempts, we simply could not hold him down. I eventually shot him... but I'm stranded here. I'm bleeding. I'm rotting.<br><br>
I am the last one left. If you are reading this note... please, spread the word, [[Level 399|far]] and [[Level 10|wide]]... [[Groups|they]] need to know. They need to warn everyone. I have to go into hiding.<br><br>
...

''Fortes Fortuna Adiuvat.''<br><br>
⠀- A bloodied note found next to a deceased [[M.E.G.]] operative — cause of death currently indeterminable.


