<span style="font-family:Montserrat"><big><big>ENTRANCES</big></big></span><br>
Entrances into '''Level 51''' include, but aren't limited to:
* Various corridors in [[Level 666]] and [[Level 909]];
* Entering doors marked with kanji symbols within [[Level 5]];
* Walking through scattered torii gates within [[Level 10]] and [[Level 55]];
* Touching or No-clipping through assorted Japanese products within [[Level 72]]; 
* No-clipping through discolored walls in [[Level 85]]; 
* And various doorways within [[Level 4]];
* A Japanese styled door in [[Level 464]] will send one here.

<span style="font-family:Montserrat"><big><big>EXITS</big></big></span><br>
Exits within '''Level 51''' include, but aren't limited to:
* Long, dimly lit hallways which gradually fade into the torii gates of [[Level 666]];
* Entering [[Level 490]] by interacting with scattered stone tablets marked with archaic symbols;
* Jumping out of an open window and into [[Level 427]]; 
* Entering through a door labeled 'τ' will lead to [[Level Tau]];
* Entering through a door labeled 'φ' will lead to [[Level Phi]];
* And noclipping directly into the floor, which may lead to [[The Void]], seldom [[The Broken|worse]].

